title: Independent candidate Akbar Ayub Khan wins PK-46 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Akbar Ayub Khan has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-46, Haripur-I by securing 68,835 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was an independent candidate Qazi Muhammad Asad Khan who bagged 28,327 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 48.18 per cent.
